@drcrallen I actually started implementing this in Plywood where plywood would issue a groupBy and then do the post processing it became hard to make all the possible queries that should work function with that workaround.

for example let's say the user sorts lexicographically on the derived dimension

Also I know I just named CONCAT() but another interesting function to implement would be [coalesce](https://dev.mysql.com/doc/refman/5.7/en/comparison-operators.html#function_coalesce) so you could do a group by on `COALESCE(`city`, `region`, `country`) AS "location"`

@navis have you read https://github.com/druid-io/druid/issues/2742?

I think some of this work is going to duplicate the work being done there and with https://github.com/druid-io/druid/issues/2292

Which is really designed to solve the use case you are targeting in a potentially more performant way.

Also, please submit proposals for changes you plan to make, especially for core code. Touching core code can really impact performance and usability of Druid in the long run.

@navis, additionally @jon-wei has tried to contact you several times to discuss this work but I don't believe you've responded to him

@fjy Wow, I really missed #2742. I thought it's something about extraction function. Wish it would be proceeded to be used with more elegant and performant way than #2217.

Currently we are participated in couple of projects using druid and I'm improvising patches needed for them and sustaining separate branch, which is making hard to PR based on master branch. I think it's best if I can make descent proposals (tried a few times) for each of PRs, but it is just not possible for me (Wish I can write English like Java).

I didn't know that @jon-wei tried to contact me but I think he is fully understanding what is needed for #2742 and what I've tried with #2217 (I think this PRs is slightly better than it). Anyway I should read #2742 first. Thanks.

